From 9a9e7c03f2ae00ddeb801f720695170eaa1d59f1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cwintlhk <howardcheng@courtwell.com.hk>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 11:35:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 03/14] cw_contacts_phase1: lookup-model service provider types
 (19.0.1.1.0)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the hardcoded service_provider_type Selection field with a
Many2one to a new cw.service.provider.type lookup model. Admins can
now add new types via the UI without a code release, and the field
is tracking-enabled so changes show in chatter.

  * New model cw.service.provider.type — name, code, sequence, active,
    description; UNIQUE on (code) and (name).
  * Seed data restores the 4 original values (Freight Forwarder,
    Inspection Company, Customs Broker, Testing Lab) as records with
    noupdate=1 so admins can rename them post-install without losing
    the override on the next module update.
  * Migration 19.0.1.1.0 — pre + post scripts read the old Selection
    column values and rewrite them as FK references to the matching
    seed records. Existing partners keep their Service Provider Type
    classification through the upgrade.
  * Field rename on res.partner: service_provider_type (Selection) ->
    service_provider_type_id (Many2one). @api.constrains and the
    contact_type cleanup onchange updated to match.
  * ACL: cw.service.provider.type is read/write/create for all
    internal users (so they can add types inline from the dropdown);
    delete restricted to base.group_system.
